{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry represents VSR (very short patch repair) endonucleases occurring in a variety of bacteria and some archaeal species, including DNA mismatch endonuclease Vsr from Escherichia coli. VSR recognises a TG mismatched base pair, generated after spontaneous deamination of methylated cytosines, and cleaves the phosphate backbone on the 5' side of the thymine [[cite:PUB00013622]]. GT mismatches can lead to C-to-T transition mutations if not repaired. VSR repairs the mismatches in favour of the G-containing strand. In Escherichia coli, this endonuclease nicks double-stranded DNA within the sequence CT(AT)GN or NT(AT)GG next to the thymidine residue, which is mismatched to 2'-deoxyguanosine [[cite:PUB00035701]]. The incision is mismatch-dependent and strand specific. The structure of VSR is similar to the core structure of restriction endonucleases, which have a 3-layer α/β/α topology [[cite:PUB00022328]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "1vsr", "name" "VERY SHORT PATCH REPAIR (VSR) ENDONUCLEASE FROM ESCHERICHIA COLI"}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR011335", "name" "Restriction endonuclease type II-like", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"cdd" {"cd00221" "Very short patch repair endonuclease"}, "pirsf" {"PIRSF018267" "Very short patch repair endonuclease"}, "ncbifam" {"TIGR00632" "DNA mismatch endonuclease Vsr"}, "pfam" {"PF03852" "DNA mismatch endonuclease Vsr"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "DNA mismatch endonuclease VSR", "short" "DNA_mismatch_endonuc_vsr"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 3, "domain_architectures" 30, "proteomes" 2368, "taxa" 11099, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 11066, "sets" 0, "proteins" 11061, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 8482}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {"gp" {"displayName" "Genome Properties",